---
title: "A logo is not a brand: what you're actually buying with an identity"
excerpt: A logo is a file. An identity is a set of rules that makes the next hundred design decisions automatic. After 25 years of drawing both, here's the difference — and why the cheap logo usually turns out to be the expensive one.
date: '2026-07-23'
category: Design
